Turkish Forces Kill PKK Regional Leader in Hatay, Sabah Reports

-- B y   S t e v e   B r y a n t
-- 
2011-04-05T05:05:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-05/turkish-forces-kill-pkk-regional-leader-in-hatay-sabah-reports.html
Turkish forces killed a Kurdish
rebel leader in fighting in the south of the country last week,
Sabah newspaper reported, without saying how it got the
information.  Aydin Baran was among seven members of the Kurdistan
Workers Party, or PKK, killed in fighting in Hatay province on
March 31, the newspaper said. Baran had been active in the PKK
for 21 years and was wanted for involvement in attacks that
killed 113 soldiers and civilians, Sabah said.  Baranâ€™s group had been spotted with thermal cameras as they
